    "rationale": "The overall credibility assessment is accepted. Eleven of thirteen credibility factors meet or exceed their required levels. The Test conditions factor (achieved level 2, required level 3) is below threshold but is accepted on the basis of corroborating analytical sensitivity evidence and the medium model risk classification. The two factors for which structured level data were not formally recorded (Model inputs, Relevance of the quantities of interest) were reviewed qualitatively and judged consistent with the medium assurance level; no substantive deficiencies were identified. The ensemble of quantitative QoI comparisons (all E/uval < 1.96, all differences < 10%) provides sufficient confidence that the FEA framework is fit for the stated context of use.",
